<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="66" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d66">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">860c.01/85½</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">29 January, 1918</hi>
                                </date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I think I see this
                            situation as a whole, and of course I am disposed to help in every way
                            possible, but I do not feel at liberty to pledge thirty thousand dollars
                            a month indefinitely. Would the Committee think it fair if I were to
                            limit the pledge to (say) six months, pending developments?</p>
                        <p>And,—another question,—is it not likely that the portion to [<hi rend="italic">the</hi>] British Government is to pay would in fact
                            be drawn from our Treasury, by loan? I feel obliged to think of the
                            financial burdens piling up on us.</p>
                        <p>Faithfully Yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>W. W.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>